- [Security Notes â€” iOS](./SECURITY_IOS.md)  

---

## ğŸŒ Web Security

### Core Principles
- HTTPS/TLS enforced with **HSTS** and redirect rules.  
- Strong **Content Security Policy (CSP)** restricts origins and prevents XSS.  
- No secrets in client code; only `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` env vars exposed.  
- Backend APIs hardened with rate limiting, input validation, and safe error handling.  
- Authentication tokens stored in HttpOnly cookies (preferred).  
- WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility standards checked in CI.  

ğŸ‘‰ See full doc:  
- [Security Notes â€” Web](./SECURITY_WEB.md)  

